snippet.title: Lukas Graham - 7 Years (Lyrics)
snippet.description:
Subscribe and press (🔔) to join the Notification Squad and stay updated with new uploads

Download Stream - http://smarturl.it/LukasGrahamAlbum

https://www.instagram.com/lukasgraham

https://www.tiktok.com/@lukasgraham

Follow Gseven Records:
Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/gsevenrecords/
Facebook : https://www.facebook.com/gsevenrecords/

We have an official permission from the right holders to upload this music

Lyrics:

[Chorus]
Once, I was seven years old, my mama told me
Go make yourself some friends, or you'll be lonely
Once, I was seven years old

[Verse 1]
It was a big, big world, but we thought we were bigger
Pushing each other to the limits, we were learning quicker
By eleven, smoking herb and drinking burning liquor
Never rich, so we were out to make that steady figure

[Chorus]
Once, I was eleven years old, my daddy told me
Go get yourself a wife, or you'll be lonely
Once, I was eleven years old

[Verse 2]
I always had that dream like my daddy before me
So I started writing songs, I started writing stories
Something about that glory just always seemed to bore me
'Cause only those I really love will ever really know me

[Chorus]
Once, I was twenty years old, my story got told
Before the morning sun, when life was lonely
Once, I was twenty years old (Lukas Graham!)

[Verse 3]
I only see my goals, I don't believe in failure
'Cause I know the smallest voices, they can make it major
I got my boys with me, at least those in favor
And if we don't meet before I leave, I hope I'll see you later

[Chorus]
Once, I was twenty years old, my story got told
I was writing 'bout everything I saw before me
Once, I was twenty years old

[Bridge]
Soon, we'll be thirty years old, our songs have been sold
We've traveled around the world and we're still roaming
Soon, we'll be thirty years old

[Verse 4]
I'm still learning about life, 
my woman brought children for me
So I can sing them all my songs, and I can tell them stories
Most of my boys are with me, some are still out seeking glory
And some I had to leave behind, 
my brother, I'm still sorry

[Chorus]
Soon, I'll be sixty years old, my daddy got sixty-one
Remember life and then your life becomes a better one
I made a man so happy when I wrote a letter once
I hope my children come and visit once or twice a month
[Breakdown]
Soon, I'll be sixty years old, will I think the world is cold?
Or will I have a lot of children who can warm me?
Soon, I'll be sixty years old
Soon, I'll be sixty years old, will I think the world is cold?
Or will I have a lot of children who can hold me?
Soon, I'll be sixty years old

[Chorus]
Once, I was seven years old, my mama told me
"Go make yourself some friends, or you'll be lonely"
Once I was seven years old
Once I was seven years old

snippet.title: Siddhartha
snippet.description:
over the stone
under the trees
together we ran
with no real plan
lookin to get free
turnin our mind
into desolation
into a no-man's land
where no man had
dared the deprivation

and i left you
or you left me
tears were cried
and part of me died
but i knew that i had to leave
and you asked me to stay
i told you I can't
well i can't be taught
what i ain't got
so it was down the road I ran

there is a man in a yellow cloak
he knows somethin i don't know
what so?

i met a girl
she taught me how to love
she turned me into a man
i forgot who I am
or i remembered who I was
and i made me a fortune
i staked out a claim
then i drank all the wine
and i rolled all the dice
and i pissed it all away

and i went to the river
to drown
but somethin in my head
said yer no good dead
why don't you jus lay down
and when I awoke
i saw my old friend
but old friends don't change
they jus get more the same
and he went down the road again

there is a man in a yellow cloak
good for him
it's getting cold

i had me a son
his mother died
she got bit by a snake
and it slithered away
but i tried to raise him right
but the boy ran off
bitterly I wept
well i looked up and down
around the town
can nothing here be kept?

there is a man in a yellow cloak
i know something he don't know

do you want to know a secret
do you want to know the truth
the river is laughing
and we're only passing
through

i said: ferryman
what is time
he said there's no such thing
listen to the stream
so i did and he said goodbye
and my old friend came
and he kissed my head
he saw all gods and men
die and live again
i guess we're never really dead

there is a man in a yellow cloak
there ain't nothing left to know

do you want to know a secret
do you want to know the truth
the river is laughing
and we're only passing
through

Led Zeppelin formed in 1968 and went on to become one of the most influential, innovative, and successful groups in modern music, having sold more than 300 million albums worldwide. The band rose from the ashes of The Yardbirds, when Jimmy Page brought in John Bonham, John Paul Jones, and Robert Plant to tour as The New Yardbirds. In 1969, Led Zeppelin released its self-titled debut which was produced by Page, as were all the subsequent albums. It marked the beginning of a 12-year reign, during which the group was widely considered to be the biggest and most innovative rock band in the world.

snippet.title: C9 vs. 100T - VCT Americas Stage 2 - Playoffs Day 4
snippet.description:
The race to Champions Paris is nearing its end. G2 Esports, the current VCT Americas champion and one of the top four teams at Masters Toronto, is the first squad to qualify via championship points for the showdown in Paris. Eleven teams are still in the fight, but only three slots remain for the Americas. A new stage is on the way  - Corrode drops in, along with a new patch, fresh comps, and new players. Will we see a new champion too? From July 18 to August 31, experience all the excitement of VCT Americas Stage 2!

In Stage 2, every team has a shot at making it through, which means the stakes are higher than ever. Some teams are coming in with revamped rosters, others are looking to continue their legacy of back-to-back Champions appearances, and a few are out to prove their place in VCT Americas is anything but temporary.
We’re proud to work with our fantastic partners throughout 2025: Aim Labs, iBUYPOWER, Pulsar, Red Bull, Samsung SSD, Secretlab, and Verizon.
